#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:1
msgid "Deprecation Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:4
msgid ""
"This page documents how to deprecate an API and mark it as no longer "
"necessary for downstream consumers of VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:7
msgid "Deprecating classes and functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:10
msgid ""
"Classes, functions, member functions and member variables may be deprecated "
"using the deprecation macros."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:12
msgid ""
"#include \"vtkDeprecation.h\" // Include the macros.\n"
"\n"
"// A deprecated class.\n"
"class VTK_DEPRECATED_IN_X_Y_Z(\"reason for deprecation\") OPT_EXPORT_MACRO "
"oldClass {\n"
"public:\n"
"  // A deprecated member function.\n"
"  VTK_DEPRECATED_IN_X_Y_Z(\"reason for deprecation\")\n"
"  void oldMemberFunction();\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"// A deprecated function.\n"
"VTK_DEPRECATED_IN_X_Y_Z(\"reason for deprecation\")\n"
"void oldFunction();\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:28
msgid ""
"The `X_Y_Z` should be the newest macro available in the `vtkDeprecation.h` "
"header when the API is added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:31
msgid ""
"Note that, unlike, the old `VTK_LEGACY_REMOVE` mechanism, the APIs are not "
"deleted. This does interfere with various kinds of deprecations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:34
msgid ""
"*Changing the return type*: Don't do this. Use a new name for the function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:36
msgid ""
"*Deprecating macros*: Use `VTK_LEGACY_REMOVE`. New macro APIs should be "
"highly discouraged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:39
msgid "Lifetime of deprecated APIs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:41
msgid ""
"Deprecated APIs should exist for at least one release with the deprecation "
"warning active. This gives consumers of VTK at least one cycle to notice the "
"deprecation and move off of it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:45
msgid ""
"Upon branching for a release, `master` will soon after have all instances of "
"deprecated symbols removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:48
msgid "Avoiding warnings within VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:50
msgid ""
"VTK is providing the deprecated symbols and as such may still use them in "
"tests or implementations. Since these generate warnings when compiling VTK "
"itself, classes which define deprecated symbols must suppress them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:54
msgid ""
"Sources which continue to use the deprecated macros should add a comment to "
"the top of the source file to hide deprecation warnings in CI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:57
msgid ""
"// Hide VTK_DEPRECATED_IN_X_Y_Z() warnings for this class.\n"
"#define VTK_DEPRECATION_LEVEL 0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:62
msgid ""
"If one already exists, please add another comment to it so that when "
"deprecated symbols are removed, it shows up in the search."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:65
msgid "Deprecation policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:67
msgid ""
"Ideally, any part of the public API of VTK, installed via its public headers "
"should be deprecated instead of being removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:70
msgid ""
"When deprecating anything, it is critical to ensure that they keep operating "
"as expected, if not, it would not be a deprecation but a bug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:73
msgid "In that regards, here is the deprecation policy:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:74
msgid "public structs/defines/enums/functions: **must** be deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:75
msgid ""
"public member variables: Should not exist but if they do, **must** be "
"deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:76
msgid "public member functions: **must** be deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:77
msgid ""
"public virtual member functions: **must** be deprecated unless in force "
"majeure case, which must be discussed with the community"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:78
msgid ""
"protected members variables: **Can just be removed** and mentioned in "
"markdown release notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:79
msgid ""
"protected member functions: **Should be deprecated** but removal and mention "
"in markdown can be acceptable in hard cases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:80
msgid ""
"protected virtual member functions: **Can be deprecated** but removal and "
"mention in markdown is also ok"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:82
msgid "Using `VTK_DEPRECATION_LEVEL`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:85
msgid ""
"When using VTK, the `VTK_DEPRECATION_LEVEL` macro may be set to a version "
"number. APIs which have been deprecated after this point will not fire (as "
"the API is not deprecated as of the level requested). It should be defined "
"using the `VTK_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch)` macro."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:90
msgid ""
"Note that APIs on the verge of deletion (those deprecated in at least one "
"release) will always raise deprecation warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/deprecation.md:93
msgid "If not set, its value defaults to the current level of VTK."
msgstr ""
